  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Ihumwa Village Subsurface Dam Construction</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project will be focused on conducting an extensive field assessment to construct two subsurface dams within the Mtumba Village- Dodoma Region. The village faces low productivity of vegetables due to limited access to water for irrigation to farmers along a seasonal river of Ihuwma. Numerous market opportunities for vegetables exist especially in Dar Es Salaam and Morogoro; however, the targeted farmers do not produce sufficient vegetable quantities throughout the year due to limited access to water. During the rainy season, water is available and farmers are able to produce vegetables in abundance and supply markets.</narrative>
  </description>
